==English==

===Etymology===
[[Islam]] and the suffix [[ism]].

===Adjective===
# Motivated by Islamic beliefs, particularly extremely authoritarian or [[fundamentalist]] interpretations. 
# (''dated'') Relating to Islam, particularly orthodox Islam.

===Noun===
# A person who espouses Islamic fundamentalist beliefs.
# (''dated'') A [[Muslim]], particularly an orthodox Muslim.
# (''somewhat rare'') A person who specializes in Islamic studies.

===Synonyms===
*[[Islamicist]] (fundamentalist senses, less commonly used)
*[[Mohammedan]] (dated term for Muslim)

